title: Shares of several financial services companies are trading higher following strong US jobs data and continued optimism amid the reopening of the economy.
Shares of several financial services companies are trading higher as equities continue to gain on optimism over the economy reopening as well as a smaller-than-expected drop in nonfarm payrolls.
